findings.title: Owner privileges (In the period when the owner is not renounced)
findings.description: The contract owner has excessive privileges even after ownership renouncement, allowing them to lock and unlock, include or exclude from rewards and fees, change tax rates, maximum transaction amounts, dev wallet addresses, enable/disable swap and liquify, change router addresses, and set minimum tokens for liquidity.

findings.title: DoS with block gas limit
findings.description: The contract may be vulnerable to a Denial of Service (DoS) attack due to the block gas limit.
